Bluming fantastic again from the Scots. Bottle from the Beer Exposed Festival. A terrificly fun event for the more adventurous beer drinker. Lots of American big beers there but for me this was the winner, smoke, fruit,wood,harmony. Well done you Scottish rebels. 
P.S. Good luck with the Portman Group.

Bottle from Website:
Bought 3 bottles from Website after press attention.
I was startled by this. Aroma, intense chocolate and dark ripe fruit, sherry
taste. deep chocolate, fruit tartness, malt sweetness and a complimentary bitterness, velvety and low carbonation
Lingering chocolate and even vanilla too.
Beuatiful if rather strong brew.

I was truly impressed with this beer.It is 2.7%abv and quite astonishing. The flavour is roasty and for the strength decent in the mouth. There is a very nice hop aroma, a little fruity and fairly bold against the malty background. Well done fellows.

Cask
Intense aroma, golden ale, nice tight head from a sparkler dispense. Light body and very refreshing. Tasty
Bottle: Absolutely stunning brew. smokey, meaty and very much chocolate. A joy
Cak at Aberedeen beer fest 2007. Delicious strong and has chocolate flavours.

Bought from Website.
Caramel and apple and a little citrus on the nose. 
Sweet fudge and more autumnal fruit on the nose. 
Dry and bitter finish leaves a slight harshness in the throught but very drinkable english / american bitter. Nice

Bought from Website.
Chocolate covered overripe fruit with an expresso on top! 
Strong imperial style stout. Hints of smoke and perhaps a little ash and more intense dark chocolate. Dry in the mouth so is easy to drink. A little burn of alcohol lets you remeber it is 8% beer your drinking. Good stuff.

Bought from Website
Beautiful. Vanilla and chocolate on the nose, Nice balance of cofee, cholcolate, oak and vanilla. Also hints of blackberries and even rasperries in the mouth. Very complex and smooth and strong! 10%abv. Superb British beer.

Nice Lager. Bottled from website order.
Moderately bitter, clean, fresh, a little bready. A little over carbonated. OK
Again a very drinkable and fruity summery ale from Oakham. Citrus striking hopsand great bitter finish. Very good

Very strong. Tastes somewhat like syrup. Good hops and bitterness try to counteract but maybee just a little too high in abv. apples. Biggest beer ive ever tasted. Deffinatley just a taste. Unusual but they are to be congratulated for being so daring. Well done.
Very nice, Fruity, fresh aroma. Drinks superbly. great summery ale  6% but still very drinkable,  dark straw in colour, hints of green fruit and burnt sugar. Great
Good summer beer. Grassy, citris aroma. fresh hops and nicely balanced ale. Nice stuff
6% IPA Floral, fruity, tastes 4%. Nice bitterness and smooth round mouth feel. Dry in the finish cleansing the palate. Good

Again a rare beer from a micro in britain. Very hoppy aroma. Orange, citrus and toffee. smooth mouthfeel, dry and balanced which makes this a pleasent drink. good bitterness but I did leave a touch of alcohol sting at the last. Good

Very interesting beer from this new scottish micro. Whisky tinged aroma with oak and vanilla also a little light and dark fruit. smoth chocolate stout with more whisky tones. very unusual but very very good.
my beer of the festival. Golden in colour with super clean fruity hop aroma. Cracking beer and drinks like a 4%. Excellent stuff.
light in colour a nice golden Hue. fruity, ripe  citrus aroma and flavour a little grassy and unpolished, but on the whole good. nice bitter aftertaste
Pretty average mild. amber in colour and slight coloured head. malty and earthy with some nice fruity tones colming through. average
pale yellow pleasant fruity hops and character. Drank at the peterborough beer fest. Very nice.
